# TypeScript Configuration

## Path Aliases
The project uses path aliases configured in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json):
- `@/*` maps to `./src/*`

## Usage Examples
```typescript
import BaseHead from "@/components/BaseHead.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "@/consts";
```

## Type Safety
- Use `CollectionEntry<"blog">` for blog post types
- Import types from `astro:content` for content collections
- Leverage Astro's built-in TypeScript support

## Configuration
- Extends `astro/tsconfigs/strict`
- Strict null checks enabled
- Includes all files except `dist/`

## Best Practices
- Always use path aliases for internal imports
- Leverage TypeScript for component props
- Use content collection types for type-safe blog handling
- Follow strict TypeScript guidelines